originalText.text: Our daughter attended Jenny's Home Family Day Care from about 6 months of age through age 5 just prior to starting Kindergarten. Jenny and her Mom are family to us. The environment at the day care is warm, loving, educational, and fun. The kids get home cooked meals each day and are guided through all of their milestones such as starting solids, nap changes, potty training, etc. We also loved that the environment was in both English and Spanish. We can not recommend them enough. I always felt like they just loved our daughter so so much, and that is just so meaningful.

originalText.text:
Jenny’s daycare was the absolute best place I’ve ever had my kids! Warm and loving, kind and teaching. My son was totally ready for prek, they helped me potty train him, fed him amazing meals (even sending some home when he was sick) and were the first caregivers for my daughter when she was a baby. My kids are older now, but Jenny and her mom still keep up with them and check in and my kids still adore them. I
Wholeheartedly recommend!
